                            <comment id="16884418" author="shestakov" created="Sat, 13 Jul 2019 17:11:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I made the pool request to fix it &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-codec/pull/23&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-codec/pull/23&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16889515" author="garydgregory" created="Sat, 20 Jul 2019 14:19:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In git master. Please verify and close. Different patch provided.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16889659" author="shestakov" created="Sun, 21 Jul 2019 06:40:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed only for DirectBuffer. But fails for HeapByteBuffer which arrayOffset() or byteBuffer.position() greater than zero or byteBuffer.remaining() is not equal byteBuffer.array().&lt;font color=&quot;#660e7a&quot;&gt;length&lt;/font&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
@Test
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void testEncodeHexByteBufferEmpty() {
    ByteBuffer zeroCapacity = allocate(0);
    ByteBuffer tenCapacity = allocate(10);
    tenCapacity.flip();
    assertEquals(zeroCapacity, tenCapacity);
    assertTrue(Arrays.equals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt;[0], Hex.encodeHex(zeroCapacity)));
    assertTrue(Arrays.equals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt;[0], Hex.encodeHex(tenCapacity)));
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fails on last assert because zeroCapacity and tenCapacity buffers are equal but Hex.encodeHex(zeroCapacity)) is not equal Hex.encodeHex(tenCapacity))&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16889660" author="shestakov" created="Sun, 21 Jul 2019 06:42:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed only for DirectBuffer. But fails for HeapByteBuffer which arrayOffset() or byteBuffer.position() greater than zero or byteBuffer.remaining() is not equal byteBuffer.array().&lt;font color=&quot;#660e7a&quot;&gt;length&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16908002" author="jameshowe" created="Thu, 15 Aug 2019 11:19:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Surely this should solve all &lt;tt&gt;ByteBuffer&lt;/tt&gt; implementation issues?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;protected&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt;[] encodeHex(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; ByteBuffer data, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt;[] toDigits) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] bytes = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[data.capacity()];
    data.get(bytes, 0, data.capacity());
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; encodeHex(bytes, toDigits);
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Arguably it should also change (or additional methods added) to consume a buffer properly, obeying position and limit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;protected&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt;[] encodeHex(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; ByteBuffer data, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt;[] toDigits) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] bytes = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[data.remaining()];
    data.get(bytes);
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; encodeHex(bytes, toDigits);
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16982672" author="alexherbert" created="Tue, 26 Nov 2019 16:55:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The current implementation converts a ByteBuffer to a byte[]. This uses the underlying array if present but does not check the remaining number of bytes in the buffer. The conversion can be changed to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] toByteArray(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; ByteBuffer byteBuffer) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; remaining = byteBuffer.remaining();
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Use the underlying buffer &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; possible
&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (byteBuffer.hasArray()) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] byteArray = byteBuffer.array();
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (remaining == byteArray.length) {
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// ***************
&lt;/span&gt;                &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// This will effectively consume the bytes !!!
&lt;/span&gt;                &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// ***************
&lt;/span&gt;                byteBuffer.position(remaining);
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; byteArray;
            }
        }
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Copy the bytes
&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] byteArray = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[remaining];
        byteBuffer.get(byteArray);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; byteArray;
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If I put the above implementation into master then it fails the current tests. The method to set the position to the limit and consume the bytes is something that is not currently assumed to occur. However it would occur if the code to copy the bytes was executed if there was no backing array.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any opinion on whether the ByteBuffer should have remaining() == 0 after use by the encode or decode methods?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16989215" author="alexherbert" created="Thu, 5 Dec 2019 22:34:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in git master.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ByteBuffer backing array is only used if the array size matches the count of bytes remaining in the buffer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
